data.name: Label243.Text
data.value:
1. Select 'Send'. 2. Select the sections you wish to upload. 3. Select the Json file with the data you want to upload. 4. Hit the 'Upload to Ram' button to upload the data to your R6581. 5. Test your R6581 and if all is good then hit the 'Commit Ram to EEprom' button to transfer the contents permanently to EEprom.
If you test does not work out for you then reset your R6581, the ram upload will be abandoned and the EEprom data will remain unchanged.

data.name: Label245.Text
data.value:
Regular calibration data management: Read/write cal constants from/to Ram. Reading previous cal data from EEProm. Eprom update command to write Ram to EEprom.
Factory calibration data management: Used during the initial setup of the instrument to eliminate small errors/artifacts. Split into DCV && AC.
Retrieve 7.2Vdc && 10kohm reference value drift history.
Previous (old) calibration constants are not extracted.

data.name: Label227.Text
data.value: Connect to device and leave in STOP position. Select Query or Send Async prior to sending command. Type command and press ENTER to send. Internal cmd's: #QA = Set to Query Async mode #SA = Set to Send Async mode

data.name: Label267.Text
data.value:
The 3458A is set up automatically at the start.
DCV calibration adjustments run through 47 readings, at reading 45 the 3458A range is changed to 100V mode, then back again.
For DCV && DCI calibration adjustments, after DCV reading 47 has finished a pop-up will prompt the user to change the 3458A inputs to 'I' and 'LO' and continue with DCI calibration adjustments.

data.name: Label280.Text
data.value: LOAD will pull saved default counts from system memory to the above && the active area. Pre-Cal will then use these values at Step 3. SAVE will save off values set manually above to system memory. If LOAD not used PDVS2mini values are used.
